An individual cannot bring a claim for unfair dismissal if they are:  
(a) Under 16, over 65, or not covered by the Redundancy Payments Acts due to age;  
(b) Working for a close relative in a private house or farm where both live in the same house or farm;  
(c) A member of the Defence Forces or Garda Síochána;  
(d) Participating in full-time training or an apprenticeship;  
(e) An officer of education and training boards, a county or city manager, or the chief executive of the HSE;  
(f) Employed under a fixed-term/specified-purpose contract that excludes unfair dismissal claims if dismissal is due to the contract ending;  
(g) Working outside the State unless certain residency conditions are met;  
(h) A statutory apprentice dismissed within 6 months of starting or 1 month before completing the apprenticeship;  
(i) An employee on probation or undergoing training for up to a year at the beginning of employment, as specified in the contract.
